  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to see if a low glycemic index diet will reduce blood sugar
      levels in pregnant women with high blood sugar levels.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Women with gestational hyperglycemia, including women with gestational diabetes and impaired
      glucose tolerance of pregnancy, consuming a low glycemic index (GI) diet will experience
      better blood glucose control thereby decreasing the risk associated complication(s).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
